Happy weekend fam! 🙌🏻

Recognition is what every true human longs for apart from money in whatever the field they choose! Whatever the field may be, there comes a point where there is no enthusiasm in what you do!

But fortunately, I was never in that phase! Even I never expected that I would get recognised in such a wide medium!
People always do what everyone does and expect big from others! But I’ve focused on SFX and 
As a gift for my dedication and passion, I’ve been recognised, honoured and awarded in a conference that was held at Phuket, Thailand on November, 2022! It’s been 2 years since it happened but I would cherish it for the rest of my life as it has been a biggest turning point in my life!

Because I represented India, I’ve taught SFX and Body painting to masters who are from 15+ Asian countries like Thailand, Korea and more!
I really deserve what I have and for everything I long for! Cause I’ve worked for it! And will be working for it! 
Of course with so much pride, I can say I’m the one who taught foreign people in a country like Thailand which is not even my homeland! May be many people could’ve organised seminars and workshops at foreign countries for Indian people! And in many cases, many foreign artists conducts seminars and workshops for Indian students! Isn’t that great that I’ve taught them? Yes, it is!😎

Conducting a conference away from motherland with the people of our state is different! But only I had the privilege to teach great masters from all fields of makeover about SFX and body painting!
It may be more than 2 years now! But the impact and positivity it created couldn’t be explained by words! 
It not only recognised and honoured my talent but also the sacrifices we make for this job as a MUA! It healed all the pains I had throughout my entire career!

Many people have done and dedicated so much things for their field! I feel very proud and grateful that I did this to my industry from south India! Of course with so much pride and happiness, I’m glad that I’m an award holder for this Asian conference. 
Trust the universe and work hard!✨

With love,
Sridevi Thiyagarajan 🧡

@loverecode Concealer and Contour Palette is a game-changer for makeup enthusiasts, yet it’s often misunderstood and underestimated. Many people look at it and dismiss its potential, not realizing that, when used correctly, this palette can deliver flawless results and elevate your makeup game.

The key to unlocking its power lies in understanding the right techniques for concealing and contouring. Here’s why this palette stands out and how to make the most of it:
	1.	Versatile Shades: The palette often features a mix of concealer shades that cater to different undertones and skin tones, along with contour shades designed for sculpting the face. What many don’t realize is that the concealers aren’t just for covering blemishes—they can also be used for brightening the under-eye area, highlighting the high points of the face, and even color correcting. The contour shades aren’t only for deepening your bone structure; they can also be blended for subtle definition and warmth.
	2.	Layering and Blending Techniques: One common mistake is not understanding how to layer products for a seamless finish. Start by applying the concealers to areas that need brightening or correction, and then layer the contour products where you want definition. The trick is to blend well—contouring is about soft shadows, not harsh lines. Using a damp beauty sponge or a contour brush, blend the product into your skin to create a natural, sculpted effect.
	3.	Understanding Your Face Shape: The power of this palette truly shines when you know your face shape and apply the concealers and contours accordingly. For example, for a more oval face shape, a soft contour along the temples and jawline can help add structure, while highlighting the center of the forehead and under the eyes brings out your features.
4.Customizable Application: Many palettes, including Recode’s, allow for customization of coverage and intensity. You can build up your contour gradually for a more natural look, or go bold for a dramatic effect. The concealer shades can be mixed to match your exact skin tone or to create a luminous highlight.
